.TH "gfs2_reservation_check_and_update" 9 "gfs2_reservation_check_and_update" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
gfs2_reservation_check_and_update \- Check for reservations during block alloc
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" gfs2_reservation_check_and_update
.BI "(struct gfs2_rbm *rbm "  ","
.BI "struct gfs2_blkreserv *rs "  ","
.BI "u32 minext "  ","
.BI "struct gfs2_extent *maxext "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "rbm" 12
The current position in the resource group
.IP "rs" 12
Our own reservation
.IP "minext" 12
The minimum extent length
.IP "maxext" 12
A pointer to the maximum extent structure
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This checks the current position in the rgrp to see whether there is
a reservation covering this block. If not then this function is a
no-op. If there is, then the position is moved to the end of the
contiguous reservation(s) so that we are pointing at the first
non-reserved block.
.SH "RETURN"
0 if no reservation, 1 if \fIrbm\fP has changed, otherwise an error
